commitResults.messageTitle: Add UiJavaFx class. Duke can now run in either CLI or GUI mode.
commitResults.messageBody:
UiJavaFx extends from Ui abstract class and buffers Duke output for later display using a MainWindow controller.
UiJavaFx allows for Duke to display a message to the user at any time, unlike previously where it can only display a message in response to a user command. Used for displaying messages on startup (e.g. a welcome message or an error message when failed to load/parse file storage).
